180вҶ’\section{The Koide Formula as Energy Balance}
181вҶ’\label{sec:koide_algebra}
182вҶ’%======================================================================
183вҶ’
184вҶ’\subsection{Charges, not masses}
185вҶ’
186вҶ’The fundamental variable is the signed mass charge $\zch = z_0 + z_i 
187вҶ’\in \mathbb{R}$, with the physical mass $m = \zch^2 \geq 0$.
188вҶ’
189вҶ’\subsection{Derivation of $Q = 2/3$}
190вҶ’
191вҶ’For three charges $\zch_k = z_0 + z_k$ with $z_0$ the mean 
192вҶ’($\sum z_k = 0$):
193вҶ’\begin{equation}
194вҶ’Q = \frac{\sum \zch_k^2}{(\sum \zch_k)^2} 
195вҶ’= \frac{3z_0^2 + \sum z_k^2}{9z_0^2}
196вҶ’= \frac{1}{3} + \frac{\langle z_k^2\rangle}{3z_0^2}\,.
197вҶ’\end{equation}
198вҶ’Therefore:
199вҶ’\begin{equation}
200вҶ’\boxed{Q = \frac{2}{3} \quad\Longleftrightarrow\quad 
201вҶ’\langle z_k^2\rangle = z_0^2\,.}
202вҶ’\end{equation}
203вҶ’
204вҶ’The two conditions are:
205вҶ’\begin{enumerate}
206вҶ’\item \textbf{Zero-sum perturbations:} $z_1 + z_2 + z_3 = 0$ 
207вҶ’(definition of $z_0$ as the mean charge).
208вҶ’\item \textbf{Energy balance:} The mean energy of the perturbations 
209вҶ’equals the energy of the unperturbed charge: 
210вҶ’$\langle z_k^2\rangle = z_0^2$.
211вҶ’\end{enumerate}
212вҶ’
213вҶ’Condition~2 is the physics. It says the splitting scale matches the
214вҶ’base scale---the coefficient of variation equals unity:
215вҶ’$\sigma(\zch)/\bar{\zch} = 1$.
216вҶ’(Dimensionally, $\zch$ has units $\MeV^{1/2}$, so
217вҶ’$z_0^2$ has units MeV---a mass scale, not an energy density.
218вҶ’The ``energy balance'' terminology is metaphorical.) This is neither perturbative 
219вҶ’($\sigma \ll \bar{\zch}$, giving $Q \to 1/3$, all equal) nor 
220вҶ’dominant ($\sigma \gg \bar{\zch}$, giving $Q \to 1$, one mass 
221вҶ’dominates). The Koide value $2/3$ is the equipartition point.
222вҶ’
223вҶ’\subsection{Why one mass can vanish}
224вҶ’
225вҶ’If $\langle z_k^2\rangle = z_0^2$, a perturbation $z_k$ can reach 
226вҶ’$|z_k| \sim z_0$, making $\zch_k = z_0 + z_k \approx 0$. A vanishing 
227вҶ’mass is the \emph{natural extreme} of energy balance, not fine-tuning.
228вҶ’
